Subject to the conditions herein, you are PERMITTED to:

1.1 View, read, and study the source code for educational purposes.
1.2 Fork this repository for personal learning and experimentation.
1.3 Modify the software for personal, non-commercial, educational use.
1.4 Use the software in authorized academic research environments.
1.5 Use the software in controlled lab environments for security research.
1.6 Benchmark CAPTCHA robustness in authorized testing environments.
1.7 Contribute improvements, bug fixes, or documentation back to the project
    via pull requests, subject to contributor guidelines.
1.8 Reference this project in academic papers with proper citation.
1.9 Include this project in a personal portfolio or resume with attribution.

